5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 Eel is a slimy fish and its skin has to be scraped with salt or sawdust to remove all traces of slime. Then it is rinsed with water. The eels are gutted, and the belly is slit beyond the vent in order to remove the kidney. All traces of blood are removed, and the eel is rinsed again. The head is left on.
5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 The processing steps, eels about 1-2 lb weight:
5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 Cleaned eels are brined in brine for 2 hours or they may be lightly salted instead.
5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 Eels are rinsed with water. The fish is impaled on a stick inserted from the stomach cavity up to behind the head.
5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 The fish is dried for 1-2 hours.
5a7e1cde-71dc-4a37-8b69-cc0fede9f4c4 Eels are hot smoked for 3 hours at 140° F (60° C) or higher. At the beginning they should be smoked at high temperature to prevent closing of the stomach cavity. After a while the fish hardens and the temperature can be lowered. To check whether the fish is cooked, press on its sides and the meat should separate from the backbone.

c53f5afd-1eb5-4dcd-94e8-ae9a7f241b81 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
c53f5afd-1eb5-4dcd-94e8-ae9a7f241b81 Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; add seasonings.
c53f5afd-1eb5-4dcd-94e8-ae9a7f241b81 Spread on fish and top with slightly beaten egg yolks.
c53f5afd-1eb5-4dcd-94e8-ae9a7f241b81 Continue baking for 8 to 10 minutes or until egg mixture is set.
c53f5afd-1eb5-4dcd-94e8-ae9a7f241b81 Garnish and serve immediately.
85238a5b-82a0-483f-a225-07997091487e Skin fillets and place in boiling salted water.
85238a5b-82a0-483f-a225-07997091487e Cover and return to boiling point; simmer 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
85238a5b-82a0-483f-a225-07997091487e Flake.
85238a5b-82a0-483f-a225-07997091487e Can be served hot with a sauce.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Cut fillets into strips about 1-inch wide and 4-inches long.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Sprinkle with salt and pepper; roll.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Cut bacon into squares and tomatoes into eighths.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Using long skewers, alternate a roll of fish, square of bacon and tomato section, until skewers are filled.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Brush with French dressing.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Place on a preheated, greased broiler pan about 3-inches from the source of heat.
c3b9cbbc-b73f-4b5c-b3a7-5ce62113d6e9 Broil 6 minutes; turn and brush with French dressing; continue boiling 5 to 6 minutes longer or until brown.
435eae0d-d985-4be4-9593-af268bb06273 Combine all ingredients and mix well.
435eae0d-d985-4be4-9593-af268bb06273 Place in a well greased loaf pan.
435eae0d-d985-4be4-9593-af268bb06273 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 40 to 45 minutes or until load is firm in the center.
435eae0d-d985-4be4-9593-af268bb06273 Unmold on a hot platter.
435eae0d-d985-4be4-9593-af268bb06273 Garnish and serve.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Add boiling water, lemon juice and sugar; stir until dissolved.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Cool.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Add vegetables, egg, seasonings and fish; mix well.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Fold in whipped cream.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Pour into mold and chill until firm.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Unmold on salad greens.
3808b487-d21e-42ef-af1a-ea42ce6e1a67 Garnish and serve with mayonnaise.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Cook onion in butter until tender.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Blend in flour and seasonings.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Add potatoes, cheese and fish.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Pour into a well greased casserole.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Prepare pastry as directed.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Cover casserole with pastry.
3bc90e62-40b8-425f-9eaa-fc22eb081f12 Bake in a hot oven, 450° F, for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Add soup and water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Add fish.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Pour into a well greased casserole.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Prepare pastry as directed.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Cover casserole with pastry.
d5b2a72c-4e41-4efd-bbf5-8ebcc925eec3 Bake in a hot oven, 450° F, for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Combine potatoes, butter, milk, seasonings and egg yolks.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Beat until light.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Add onion, parsley and fish.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Pour into 6 well greased individual casseroles.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Place in a pan of water and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
e7c1415c-b905-4cc0-b211-0a95f2f0b4ba Garnish and serve hot.
2cfdbbba-308a-4487-acfe-512540bbd12d Combine all ingredients, except lettuce, being careful not to break the fish into too small pieces.
2cfdbbba-308a-4487-acfe-512540bbd12d Chill.
2cfdbbba-308a-4487-acfe-512540bbd12d Serve in lettuce cups.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Cool.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Blend mayonnaise, ketchup and lemon juice.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Combine all ingredients except salad greens; mix well.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Pour into mold and chill until firm.
ba792dbe-b2bb-4164-a409-765107ccb151 Unmold on salad greens and garnish.
4b4dc1b0-794c-4b26-86f7-d26052de15d6 Combine fish, half of sandwich spread, salt and pepper.
4b4dc1b0-794c-4b26-86f7-d26052de15d6 Spread 6 slices of toast with fish mixture; arrange egg, lettuce and remaining sandwich spread between other slices.
4b4dc1b0-794c-4b26-86f7-d26052de15d6 Fasten layers together with toothpicks.
4b4dc1b0-794c-4b26-86f7-d26052de15d6 Cut into quarters.
4b4dc1b0-794c-4b26-86f7-d26052de15d6 Garnish and serve.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Combine egg, salt and pepper.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Dip fish in egg and roll in crumbs.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Place fish in a heavy frying pan which contains about one-eighth inch of fat, hot but not smoking.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Fry at a moderate heat.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 When fish is brown on one side, turn carefully and brown other side.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Cooking time is about 10 minutes, depending on thickness of fish.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Drain on absorbent paper.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Cut rolls in half and remove some of the soft inside center.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Combine relish, onion, mayonnaise and mustard; spread on rolls.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Place fried fish on rolls, top with tomatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Replace tops.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Wrap each sandwich in wax paper.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Heat in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through.
427ccc98-3d89-40c2-b67e-d7357c244455 Serve hot.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Skin fillets and cut into 1/2 inch pieces.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Cut a thin slice from the top of each pepper and remove seeds.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Simmer peppers in boiling salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or until almost tender.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Drain.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Fry bacon until crisp; add onion, celery, chili sauce, seasonings and fish.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Simmer about 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Fill peppers with fish mixture.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top of peppers.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Place in a well greased baking dish.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
08ed6ad0-0362-4f71-b1e5-40d3940f78ca Garnish and serve hot.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 To the tomato juice, add 1/2 cup of celery and the onion, parsley, vinegar, cloves, sugar, salt and pepper; simmer for 15 minutes.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Strain.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Cool.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Add the remaining celery, relish, egg and fish.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Pour into mold and chill until firm.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Unmold on salad greens.
0cfcb30f-b9a8-4d8d-862d-b184a3d53682 Garnish and serve with mayonnaise.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Skin fillets and cut into 1-inch pieces.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Add onion and celery; cook until tender and slightly brown.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Add water, seasonings and rice; cook 10 minutes.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Add fish; cook 10 minutes longer or until rice and fish are tender.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Add tomato juice; heat.
17a718a3-2082-4979-bc4b-9e9d5acf9f5a Serve immediately with chopped parsley over the top.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Skin fillets and sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Line 12 well greased muffin tins with fillets, overlapping ends of fillets.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Place ball of stuffing in center of each.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Brush tops with butter and place 1/4 slice of bacon on each.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
21166fe3-dd03-4c9b-bea9-171c37175ac9 Serve on a hot platter, plain or with a sauce.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Drain and flake salmon.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Cook green pepper, onion and pimiento in butter until tender.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Blend in flour and seasonings.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Stir a little of the hot sauce into the beaten egg yolks and add to the sauce, stirring constantly.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Add salmon and mushrooms; heat thoroughly.
bdeae637-abc7-4ead-a3cc-5de79cde619f Serve in toast cups, patty shells or on toast.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Sprinkle salmon on both sides with salt and pepper.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Place in a well greased baking dish.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Combine mushrooms, butter, lemon juice and onion.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Pour over the salmon.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
6a6bb1a8-6b87-4c9a-b8eb-d6a9653550d9 Serve immediately on a hot platter.
8d776df0-e87d-4054-a09d-dad7716220fc Remove skin from fillet and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of salt.
8d776df0-e87d-4054-a09d-dad7716220fc Place in a shallow, well greased baking pan or casserole.
8d776df0-e87d-4054-a09d-dad7716220fc Combine sour cream and seasonings; pour over salmon.
8d776df0-e87d-4054-a09d-dad7716220fc Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 30 to 35 minutes.
8d776df0-e87d-4054-a09d-dad7716220fc Garnish and serve.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Wash and dry salmon.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Sprinkle inside and out with salt.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Stuff fish loosely and sew opening with needle and string, or close with skewers.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Place fish in a well greased baking pan.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Arrange bacon slices on fish and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 40 to 60 minutes or until fish flakes easily from the bone when tested with a fork.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 If fish seems dry while baking, baste occasionally with drippings or melted fat.
0238bbd3-2bed-451f-b113-c579980ed2f4 Remove string or skewers and serve immediately on a hot platter, plain or with a sauce.
3861e4c4-7ffc-431e-bf7d-5d93ea5abbcf Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
3861e4c4-7ffc-431e-bf7d-5d93ea5abbcf Melt butter and blend in flour and seasonings.
3861e4c4-7ffc-431e-bf7d-5d93ea5abbcf Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
3861e4c4-7ffc-431e-bf7d-5d93ea5abbcf Add salmon and eggs; heat.
3861e4c4-7ffc-431e-bf7d-5d93ea5abbcf Serve over rice or in a rice ring.
106df836-79a0-420e-8516-51351eb8747b Arrange fish, skin side up, on preheated, well greased broiler pan about 4 inches from source of heat.
106df836-79a0-420e-8516-51351eb8747b Broil for 7 minutes.
106df836-79a0-420e-8516-51351eb8747b Turn, baste with butter and sprinkle with pepper.
106df836-79a0-420e-8516-51351eb8747b Broil 5 minutes longer or until brown.
106df836-79a0-420e-8516-51351eb8747b Serve with egg sauce.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Sprinkle both sides of steaks with salt and pepper.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Add rosemary and vinegar to the salad oil; shake well and let stand at room temperature for an hour or longer; strain.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Dip fish in oil mixture and place on a preheated, greased broiler pan about 2 inches from the heat.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Broil 5 to 8 minutes or until slightly brown.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Baste with oil and turn carefully.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Brush other side with oil and cook 5 to 8 minutes more or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
af727453-f865-4767-af71-3ab0720368b2 Serve immediately.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf Cut fish into serving size portions and sprinkle with half of the salt and pepper.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf In a large, well greased casserole place in layers the corn, beans and potatoes, sprinkling each layer with the remaining salt and pepper.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf Combine butter, lemon juice, onion and parsley.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf Dip salmon into mixture and arrange on top of potatoes.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf Cover with tomato slices and grated cheese.
6ca27545-6502-4ab9-998e-10d866e282bf Bake in moderate oven, 350° F, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour and one-quarter teaspoon salt.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Arrange half of the salmon in a shallow, well greased casserole.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Combine bread crumbs and remaining ingredients; mix well.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Arrange half of the crumb mixture over salmon; add remaining salmon.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Pour sauce over ingredients in the casserole and top with remaining crumb mixture.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
54b8fa09-166a-41bd-81a8-fe3644c166df Serve immediately.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Drain and flake salmon.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Combine sauce, pimiento, corn and eggs.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Place one-third of macaroni in well greased casserole, cover with one-third of fish and one-third of sauce mixture.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Repeat until all of the ingredients are used.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
d8ab9bcb-83ce-4230-bafa-899557a57130 Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Melt butter and blend in flour.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Arrange potatoes, salmon and sauce in alternate layers in a well greased casserole.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Combine remaining ingredients and spread over the top of the fish mixture.
235b710e-d4a3-4bd8-9ac6-018d410af7e3 Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 30 minutes.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Cut salmon into half-inch cubes.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Fry bacon until crisp and brown.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Add water and potatoes; cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are partially tender.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Add salmon and simmer for 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Add milk and seasonings; heat.
dde3e7cb-98de-471d-a88f-1a66342bb8c8 Serve immediately with chopped parsley sprinkled over the top.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Drain and flake salmon.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Combine with celery, sweet pickle, onion and mayonnaise.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Spread six slices of bread with fix mixture; cover each with a second slice of bread and place tomatoes and lettuce on each; cover with the remaining six slices of bread.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Fasten sandwiches with toothpicks.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Cut into quarters.
1874dff5-e842-4422-9e63-bcdf8d388765 Garnish and serve.
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Add 2.2 lbs of salt to 1 gallon of water. This makes 80 degrees brine. Place the brine in a cooler.
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Place salmon fillets in 80 degrees brine for 6 – 12 hours, depending on the size of the fillets.
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Remove fish from the brine and rinse for 1 hour under cold running water
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Place on smoking rack and dry the fish (3 hours).
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Smoke with cold smoke (below 70° F, 22° C) for about 16 hours.
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Remove the fish from the smoker and cool it.
b2fa5677-6b01-4d60-a8df-2f1d6267481c Keep refrigerated.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Remove skin and bones from salmon and grind twice.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Stir into hot water and simmer gently for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Add onion, celery, parsley and green pepper to milk.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Scald and strain.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Add scalded milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Add the salmon mixture.
38ac7de0-65fc-4129-8c6e-93a3e09154ac Heat and serve immediately with chopped parsley sprinkled over the top.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Cut salmon into serving size pieces.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Using a small Dutch oven or deep frying pan with lid, cook onion and celery in the fat until tender.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Add all ingredients except fish and rice and simmer for a half hour.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Remove lemon, garlic and bay leaf.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Arrange fish in the sauce and simmer without stirring for a half hour.
b55c4d4d-1656-42a9-b87f-db608c0d8d7f Serve over cooked rice.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Melt butter and blend in flour.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Add the Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Combine all ingredients except butter and crumbs; mix well.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Place in individual, well greased casseroles.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over casseroles.
3446151b-de57-4ac4-837f-9752df80bb8a Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for about 20 minutes or until brown.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Melt butter and blend in flour and seasonings.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Stir in cheese and heat until melted.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Combine salmon with rice, peas and cheese sauce.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Place mixture in a well greased casserole.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
defbf8be-6b97-49a6-82cf-2f7e896e7713 Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 30 minutes or until brown.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Add 2.2 lbs of salt to 1 gallon of water. This makes 80 degrees brine. Cool brine in a cooler.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Place salmon fillets for 1 hour in 80 degrees brine.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Remove the fish from the brine and rinse it under cold running water.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Soak in cold water for 10 minutes.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Place the fish on a rack and dry for two hours
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Apply hot smoke gradually increasing the temperature of the smokehouse.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Hold at 150° F (66° C) internal temperature for 30 minutes. To achieve this your smoker’s temperature will have to be higher, around 170° F.
72642128-01b6-45c9-84ed-fcfe5a306d94 Remove the fish from the smoker and cool it.
c5e30f18-abe6-4c37-a0f5-6b4b549d6113 Cut the salmon into 1-inch cubes.
c5e30f18-abe6-4c37-a0f5-6b4b549d6113 Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cubed salmon and marinate for 1-1/2 hours.
c5e30f18-abe6-4c37-a0f5-6b4b549d6113 Remove from sauce and place on skewers.
c5e30f18-abe6-4c37-a0f5-6b4b549d6113 Place skewers across a baking dish and bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for about 20 minutes.
c5e30f18-abe6-4c37-a0f5-6b4b549d6113 Baste once during baking with extra sauce.
84ac65e4-8023-4c67-b043-9689defb8be9 Drain and flake salmon.
84ac65e4-8023-4c67-b043-9689defb8be9 Combine ingredients in top of a double boiler and heat over hot water.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Combine all ingredients except eggs and liquid.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Mix well and place in a well greased loaf pan.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Combine the beaten eggs and liquid.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Pour over the salmon mixture in the loaf pan.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 45 minutes or until loaf is firm in the center.
e183af38-b0a4-49ff-af33-ae7b1bc6956a Unmold on a hot platter and serve plain or with a sauce.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Sprinkle salmon on both sides with 1 teaspoon salt and place in a well greased casserole with celery, onion, green pepper and lemon.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Add the water; cover and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 30 minutes or until salmon flakes easily when tested with a fork.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Allow salmon to chill thoroughly in the liquid.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Strain the liquid from the salmon and add water to make 1-1/2 cups.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup of the salmon liquid for 5 minutes and dissolve over hot water.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Add to the liquid and mix well.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Cut salmon into 1/4-inch cubes.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Add salmon, celery, green pepper, parsley, onion, lemon juice and remaining salt to the gelatin mixture.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Pour into a large loaf pan and chill until firm.
5d152dd0-d395-423e-8d91-b6ac3bc7bd71 Unmold on lettuce and serve with a sauce made by combining mayonnaise and sweet pickle.
24ab7793-7db0-4fff-b682-3324ed4b0122 Combine all of the ingredients except water.
24ab7793-7db0-4fff-b682-3324ed4b0122 Place in a well greased casserole and pour water over top.
24ab7793-7db0-4fff-b682-3324ed4b0122 Cover tightly and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 1-1/2 hours.
24ab7793-7db0-4fff-b682-3324ed4b0122 Turn out on a hot platter and serve plain or with a sauce.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Sprinkle salmon on both sides with 1 teaspoon salt and dash pepper.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Roll in flour and brown steaks quickly in fat.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Place the browned steaks in a large, well greased casserole.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Cook celery, onion and green pepper in the remaining fat until almost tender.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Add corn and soy sauce; pour over the salmon.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Sprinkle with remaining salt and bake covered in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 25 to 30 minutes.
c4390359-23c8-45f3-a565-5891c7d23c93 Serve from casserole.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Cut fish into 1-inch cubes and sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Prepare the biscuit as directed.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Roll one-eighth inch thick and line 6 individual casseroles.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Divide fish into casseroles.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Combine the white sauce, peas and shrimp; pour over fish in the casseroles.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Cover each with a top crust.
e5f806e8-bfd6-4e03-86dc-9887f06b485b Bake in a hot oven, 450° F, for 20 minutes or until brown.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Cut the salmon into one half inch cubes.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Cook corn meal, water and 1-1/4 teaspoons of the salt over boiling water for 30 minutes.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Pour into a loaf pan and allow to set.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Cook green pepper and onion in 3 tablespoons of the butter for 5 minutes.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Add tomatoes, remaining salt and chili powder.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Simmer 20 minutes.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Add salmon cubes to the tomato mixture and simmer 10 minutes longer.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Make a paste of the flour and remaining 2 tablespoons of butter; stir into the mixture.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Add ripe olives.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Line a well greased casserole with one-eighth to one-quarter inch thick slices of corn meal.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Pour in salmon mixture; cover with remaining slices of corn meal.
83fc1748-6b90-4584-b368-739f604a0e06 Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for about 40 minutes or until brown.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Salt salmon on both sides.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Arrange onion, lemon, spices and garlic on bottom of a well greased casserole.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Place the salmon, skin side up, over the seasonings; cover tightly and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 1 hour.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Chill salmon in casserole.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Place on serving platter and remove skin carefully.
acf9ceb5-2682-4cb7-a345-5785efacce45 Garnish with mayonnaise and cucumber.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Drain and flake salmon.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Beat the milk, butter, seasonings and beaten egg yolks into the mashed potatoes.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Stir in the fish and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Place in a well greased casserole.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
1b91453c-66e3-47b2-9905-813dcbd4dc0e Bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 45 minutes or until brown.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Cut salmon into one-fourth inch cubes and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Combine butter, lemon juice and onion.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Pour over the salmon and toss lightly until fish is evenly coated with butter mixture.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Prepare biscuit according to directions and roll into a rectangle about one-fourth inch thick.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Spread salmon mixture evenly over the surface and roll as for a jelly-roll.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Seal the ends.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Place on a well greased baking sheet and cut several diagonal slashes across top.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Brush with milk and bake in a moderate oven, 375° F, for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
ca8173c9-5ad9-4275-9250-e6a41ace5eda Serve plain or with a sauce.
68c788e4-26c5-42b4-8076-43ed88a9b299 Drain and flake salmon.
68c788e4-26c5-42b4-8076-43ed88a9b299 Combine all ingredients except lettuce, being careful not to break the fish into too small pieces.
68c788e4-26c5-42b4-8076-43ed88a9b299 Serve in lettuce cups and garnish.
8a54710c-293b-4b02-897a-47bb45ccc97d In a bowl mix the salmon, celery and capers with the mayonnaise.
8a54710c-293b-4b02-897a-47bb45ccc97d Season with salt and lemon juice, continue mixing.
8a54710c-293b-4b02-897a-47bb45ccc97d Arrange the leaves of lettuce to form a nest in the salad bowl.
8a54710c-293b-4b02-897a-47bb45ccc97d Place the mixture in the center and garnish with paprika.
864efff0-2807-435a-a2e2-6f6c7cef137b Remove skin and bones from salmon and arrange on a bed of lettuce.
864efff0-2807-435a-a2e2-6f6c7cef137b Spread mayonnaise over the salmon.
864efff0-2807-435a-a2e2-6f6c7cef137b Sprinkle the chopped parsley and sprinkle paprika on top.
864efff0-2807-435a-a2e2-6f6c7cef137b Arrange a border of shrimp, olives, sliced lemon, and rings of hard boiled eggs around the salmon.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Drain and flake salmon.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Combine the first four ingredients.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes and dissolve over hot water.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Stir into mayonnaise.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Add sour cream, onion, salt, lemon juice and parsley.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Combine with fish mixture.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Place in a ring mold and chill until firm.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Unmold on a bed of lettuce and fill center with the tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
2f42a4f8-728f-4ceb-bc4c-28b6de9990b8 Serve with mayonnaise.
f6064af3-c4d1-4576-8c7c-2502916c54ae Drain and flake salmon.
f6064af3-c4d1-4576-8c7c-2502916c54ae Combine all ingredients except tomatoes, salt and lettuce.
f6064af3-c4d1-4576-8c7c-2502916c54ae Cut centers from tomatoes, salt lightly and fill with the salmon mixture.
f6064af3-c4d1-4576-8c7c-2502916c54ae Serve in lettuce cups.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Blend lemon juice and onion into salmon.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and butter.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Sprinkle one-third of this mixture in a well greased casserole; cover with a layer of the salmon mixture.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Repeat layers ending with crumbs.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Pour heated liquid over all.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 30 minutes or until brown.
ef0ea170-2d1c-4123-b5f0-794cd71fa5bf Serve plain or with a sauce.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Drain fish and grind twice.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Cream the cheese and mayonnaise.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Blend in fish, celery and seasonings.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Remove crusts from bread.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Cut each slice into 3 strips and toast.
943630ec-400a-4519-b817-c58e712259b1 Spread salmon on toast strips and garnish.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Drain and flake salmon.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Add seasonings and mayonnaise; blend into a paste.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Divide in half; roll very thin in circle about 9 inches in diameter.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Spread with salmon mixture.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Cut into wedge-shaped pieces and roll in jelly-roll fashion beginning at the round edge.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Score top of rolls with a fork and sprinkle with paprika.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Bake in a hot oven, 425° F, for about 15 minutes or until brown.
da4c4408-d2db-410c-bed6-9481547f4348 Serve hot or cold.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Drain and flake salmon, saving liquid.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Add liquid gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Stir a little of the hot sauce into beaten egg yolks and add to sauce, stirring constantly.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Add salmon.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Fold gently into salmon mixture.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Pour into well greased casserole and bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 45 minutes.
adccac21-488d-4f59-bead-16607bd23432 Serve immediately, plain or with a sauce.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Drain tuna.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Break into large pieces.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Cook green pepper in butter until tender.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Add pimiento and tuna; heat.
54a4a29c-9d05-441f-85ad-40dd8a8a1a99 Serve on corn bread, biscuits, or toast.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Drain tuna.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Break into large pieces.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Cook onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Blend in flour and brown.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Add bouillon gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Add remaining ingredients, except rice; heat.
dae224b3-ccac-42c5-a215-40f3c38298a6 Serve over rice.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Drain tuna.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Flake.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Add soup, pimiento, green pepper and seasoning; blend into a paste.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Spread on crackers.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Sprinkle with cheese.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Place on a cooky sheet, 15-1/2 x 12 inches.
f58135c2-f4f1-45ab-93ee-1b395de8d1a5 Broil about 3 inches from source of heat for 5 minutes or until cheese browns.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Drain tuna.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Flake.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Add celery and mayonnaise; blend into a paste.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Combine butter and horseradish.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Spread horseradish butter on toast points.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Top with tuna mixture.
6c91a760-4f06-4ea7-8383-ace7467da59b Garnish with parsley sprinkled over the top.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Drain tuna. Break into large pieces.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Cook asparagus as directed on package; drain.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Arrange asparagus in a well greased baking pan, 11 x 7 x 1-1/2 inches.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Cover with tuna.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Fry almonds in butter until lightly browned.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Blend in flour and seasonings.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Add sherry.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Pour over tuna and asparagus.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Sprinkle with paprika.
3e7d211c-b96f-47a2-bd95-bbca126812c1 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 25 to 30 minutes.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Drain tuna. Break into large pieces.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Combine all ingredients except paprika.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Place in a well greased, 2-quart casserole.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Sprinkle with paprika.
74fe893c-a342-423d-9345-44bf5b4a1da9 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 50 minutes.
ee5e64db-414f-4c46-b18f-2c4706b7c1c8 Drain tuna. Break into large pieces.
ee5e64db-414f-4c46-b18f-2c4706b7c1c8 Add onion, lemon juice, parsley and garlic salt.
ee5e64db-414f-4c46-b18f-2c4706b7c1c8 Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.

4f5ddd5c-2e55-4136-b196-7b837d1a071b Serve with a cocktail sauce.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Cut large shrimp in half. Wash tomatoes.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Remove stem ends and centers; sprinkle with salt.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Combine rice, cheese, egg, seasonings and shrimp.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Place in tomatoes.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top of tomatoes.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Place in a well greased baking dish.
7ca5c21d-1fb8-4cc6-9770-34ac9ee37e35 Bake in a moderate oven, 350° F, for 20 to 25 minutes or until tomatoes are tender.
d028ae4c-f162-41c8-bbf1-c5a2f013a8a6 Peel shrimp and remove sand veins.
d028ae4c-f162-41c8-bbf1-c5a2f013a8a6 Wash and cut into small pieces.
d028ae4c-f162-41c8-bbf1-c5a2f013a8a6 Cook onion, parsley and shrimp in butter until tender.
d028ae4c-f162-41c8-bbf1-c5a2f013a8a6 Combine egg, milk and seasonings.
d028ae4c-f162-41c8-bbf1-c5a2f013a8a6 Mix all ingredients together until well moistened.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Cut large shrimp in half.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Fry mushrooms in butter for about 5 minutes.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Blend in flour and seasonings; add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Stir in shrimp.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Fill 6 individual well greased shells or casseroles.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Sprinkle with cheese paprika.
dc58bb5a-849a-4c3b-913e-ca9f37c7af58 Bake in a hot oven, 400° F, for 10 minutes or until cheese browns.

794bda3d-5c3e-43b9-a978-4ec71f37e05c Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold tomato juice for 5 minutes.

794bda3d-5c3e-43b9-a978-4ec71f37e05c Add next 6 ingredients and shrimp.

cde8cd57-20c9-4450-b4dc-2c31df62ae53 Combine all ingredients, except pastry mix and cream; blend into a paste.

cde8cd57-20c9-4450-b4dc-2c31df62ae53 Prick tops and brush with cream.
